begin_memory_text: We exchanged names, where we lived and where we were born.  Khia spoke about her education and where she has traveled to.  I spoke about my home and where we had been stationed while husband was in the military.
middle_memory_text: Spoke about her wife and when she got married and her profession.  We spoke about my homestead, my animals and killing chickens.
end_memory_text: We spoke about Covid, what is going on in the world today and how the election will be handled.  We also spoke about whether or not her and her wife would be having children.
rest_of_day_open: Pretty boring.  I am redoing all the shelves in my kitchen and restocking them.  I am also expecting a couch delivery on Monday, so I need to get the Game Room redone as well so the couch will fit in there.  I I have a ton of laundry that needs folding and 2 vet appointments for our youngest cat.
critical_positive: Everything worked well.  We both had interesting lives to share.  We both were open and honest.  Khia seems like the type of person I would like to have as a good friend.  I would like to know more about her life and her interests, and about her time in other countries like Kenya.
critical_negative: I really don't think anything didn't work.  I think maybe I should have let her speak more, but I wanted to make certain we had enough to conversate about.  I do wish I could have asked her more questions about her work and home life, and of her travels around the world.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, we talked about where we were from, and gave a little background information. We then moved on to talking about random stuff.
middle_memory_text: We talked about being married, killing chickens, living on the farm, a little bit of COVID talk, and what we had for dinner.
end_memory_text: Drinking, what else she wants to do with the farm, benefits living in rural areas, having children, being a good mom
rest_of_day_open: Today is Thursday and today is the day I purchased my first home with my wife. The rest of the week will be lots of talk about the house and this weekend will be spent cleaning the house. We are in a good mood overall and I imagine that it will continue.
critical_positive: We vibed well. We found connections and took it from there. We were interested in each other and tried to learn a little more. We were honest and open about ourselves to a certain degree, which helped make the conversation feel genuine. We are two nice people who just wanted to chat and make a little money.
critical_negative: The audio lagged a bit and didn't work initially. I could hear myself speak and it was a bit delayed so it made for a bit of talking over each other or jokes being delivered a little late. The conversation wasn't as smooth as I would like but we still made it work.
